  "local_port": 46616,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you make mulled wine?",
  "response": "Mulled wine is a warm, spiced beverage that is perfect for cold weather. Here's a basic recipe to help you make it:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- 1 bottle of red wine (750 ml)\n- 1 orange, sliced\n- 8-10 whole cloves\n- 2-3 cinnamon sticks\n- 2-4 tablespoons of honey or sugar (adjust to taste)\n- 1/4 cup brandy (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon of whole allspice (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon of ground nutmeg (optional)\n- Additional spices like star anise or cardamom pods (optional)\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Prepare the Orange**:\n   - Slice the orange into rounds and stud a few of the slices with whole cloves.\n\n2. **Combine Ingredients**:\n   - In a large pot or slow cooker, pour in the bottle of red wine. Add the orange slices with cloves, cinnamon sticks, honey or sugar, and any optional spices you may be using.\n\n3. **Heat the Mixture**:\n   - Warm the mixture over medium heat until it is just below simmering. Do not let it boil, as this can cook off the alcohol and affect the flavor.\n   - If you are using a slow cooker, set it to low heat.\n\n4. **Add Brandy**:\n   - If you are using brandy, add it to the pot and stir to combine.\n\n5. **Simmer**:\n   - Allow the mulled wine to gently simmer for at least 20 minutes to allow the flavors to meld together. You can let it simmer for up to an hour for a more intense flavor.\n\n6. **Taste and Adjust**:\n   - Taste the mulled wine and adjust the sweetness or spices as needed.\n\n7. **Serve**:\n   - Strain the mulled wine to remove the solid spices and orange slices. Serve warm in heatproof glasses or mugs.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Choice of Wine**: Use a decent red wine that you enjoy drinking, but it doesn't have to be expensive. A medium-bodied wine works well.\n- **Sweetness**: Adjust the sweetness to your preference. You can use honey, sugar, or even maple syrup.\n- **Garnish**: Garnish with additional orange slices, a cinnamon stick, or star anise for a festive touch.\n\nEnjoy your warm and cozy mulled wine!",
